Host US singer-songwriter Alicia Keys arrives for the 61st Annual Grammy Awards on February 10, 2019, in Los Angeles. JOHANNESBURG - Award-winning musician Alicia Keys will take center stage once again as the host of the 62nd annual Grammy Awards in January 2020. The 38-year-old will be returning to host the awards for a second year in a row. READ: Alicia Keys applauded for Grammy performance Nominations for the music awards show will be announced on Wednesday, November 20. The 2020 Grammys will take place on January 26th from the Staples Center in Los Angeles, California. When you're about to host the 2020 GRAMMYs and your only competition is yourself!